    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">719.21/57</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Colombian, Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Olaya</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Latin American
                        Affairs, Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1063</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. White</hi>: Referring to your esteemed letter
                    of the 12th inst., and to our last conversation in your office, I take pleasure
                    in advising you that my Government approves the text of the Procès Verbal for
                    initiating regular diplomatic relations between Colombia and Panama as submitted
                    by the Department of State, and authorizes me to sign it.</p>
                <p>It gives me great pleasure to have reached this happy result and trusting to hear
                    from you in the matter, I await your commands and remain,</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Enrique Olaya</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
